    <h1>About the River Ranger</h1>
<h5>Embracing the ethos of summer camp, becoming a River Ranger puts you in touch with others who are interested in wildlife, preservation and recreation all to do with the Ottawa River and its Watershed. </h5>
  <div>
  
      <%= image_tag('watershed.jpg', alt: "Ottawa watershed") %>
  <p class="caption">This is the Ottawa River Watershed</p>
  <h2>River Rangers are...</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Residents who live along the river and its watershed</li>
    <li>Kids who want to learn about ecology</li>
    <li>Concerned citizens who want to keep the river healthy</li>
    <li>Long-time RiverKeeper water testers</li>
    <li>Researchers who wish to share their findings with the public</li>
  </ul> 
</div>
<div>
  <h2>What you can do</h2>
  <ul>
      <li>Record observations using photos, badges, and comments and link them to a location</li>
      <li>Testers can enter in pH, Temperature, Phosphates, Dissolved Oxygen, Nitrites, Nitrates, and E-coli</li>
      <li>Researchers can add links to their work as well as the synopsis and date published</li>
      <li>See what other observations are nearby</li>
      <li>Confirm others' observations with your own</li>
      <li>Conservation authorities are notified of any signs of trash, red blooms or invasive species</li>
      <li>Define your own area of interest <em>Coming soon!</em></li>
  </ul>
